  "text": "The electrophysiological demonstrations for a separate activity of MC and PC pathways in humans were obtained by varying the spatial frequencies and the time of stimuli presentation [CITATION_1] . The differential properties of the MC and PC pathways make it possible to infer the relative role of those pathways in the capacity to discriminate contrast levels at different spatial patterns, usually evaluated by the contrast sensitivity function measurement.",
